   "source": [
    "-- Write your PostgreSQL query statement below\n",
    "SELECT A.id\n",
    "FROM Weather A\n",
    "JOIN Weather B\n",
    "  ON A.recordDate = B.recordDate + INTERVAL '1 day'\n",
    "WHERE A.temperature > B.temperature;\n",
    "\n",
    "Learned\n",
    "- Interval for calculating over time (postgreSQL) WHERE (end_date - start_date) > INTERVAL '5' DAY; You can find records with a duration greater than a specific interval:\n",
    "- SQL operates row-by-row. A single row has no built-in knowledge of “the previous row” unless you explicitly connect it to one."
   ]
  },
