   "source": [
    "SELECT r.contest_id,ROUND((COUNT(DISTINCT r.user_id) / (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) FROM Users) * 100.0),2) AS percentage\n",
    "FROM Register r\n",
    "    LEFT JOIN Users u ON r.user_id = u.user_id\n",
    "GROUP BY r.contest_id\n",
    "ORDER BY percentage DESC, r.contest_id ASC\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "When grouping:\n",
    "\t•\tAnything inside COUNT() from the joined table is already filtered by the group.\n",
    "\t•\tA subquery (or CTE) runs independently of the grouping.\n",
    "\n",
    "So ask yourself: “Does this value depend on the group, or is it global?”\n",
    "\n",
    "If it’s global → use subquery/CTE.\n",
    "If it’s per group → use aggregate directly.\n",
    "\n",
    "    DONT NEED JOIN AT ALL -->\n",
    "SELECT \n",
    "    r.contest_id,\n",
    "    ROUND(\n",
    "        COUNT(DISTINCT r.user_id) \n",
    "        / (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) FROM Users)\n",
    "        * 100.0,\n",
    "    2) AS percentage\n",
    "FROM Register r\n",
    "GROUP BY r.contest_id\n",
    "ORDER BY percentage DESC, r.contest_id ASC;\n"
   ]
  },
